Author-Name: ERNAN HARUVY 
Author-Name: CHARLES N. NOUSSAIR 
Title: The Effect of Short Selling on Bubbles and Crashes in Experimental Spot Asset Markets 
Abstract:
 A series of experiments illustrate that relaxing short-selling constraints
 lowers prices in experimental asset markets, but does not induce prices to
 track fundamentals. We argue that prices in experimental asset markets are
 influenced by restrictions on short-selling capacity and limits on the
 cash available for purchases. Restrictions on short sales in the form of
 cash reserve requirements and quantity limits on short positions behave in
 a similar manner. A simulation model, based on <link rid="b7">DeLong et
 al. (1990)</link>, generates average price patterns that are similar to
 the observed data. Copyright 2006 by The American Finance Association. 
